Job Description:
We are currently looking for trained and motivated fully qualified and certified Vietnamese Tax Advisors with the responsibilities outlined below:

- Providing advisory services and tax-efficient solutions to international clients on different (cross-border) taxation matters, such as:
• FCWT, VAT, PIT, CIT, Import-Export taxes;
• Transfer Pricing;
• Tax due diligence in M&A projects;
• Tax advice for foreign investments and transactions;
• Tax incentives for investment projects;
• Cross-border taxation, tax treaties, global minimum tax, and
• Other individuals/organization's tax issues to minimize tax risks.
- Drafting legal opinions on tax law related matters for clients;
- Regularly update on tax regulations and ensure that the tax advisory services provided to clients are at the highest level of tax effectiveness, compliant with current laws and regulations of Vietnam, as well as compatible with clients’ commercial practices;
- Represent clients in exchanges with local tax authorities and achieve optimal results for the benefit of the clients’ business;
- Draft, manage, and carry out tax filings with relevant Vietnamese state authorities on behalf of clients;
- Maintain good communication with clients, as well as other internal and external stakeholders, efficiently respond to questions and advise on tax compliance in Vietnam;
- Identify significant issues/risks from daily transactions of client’s activities, timely raise the issues and propose solutions to the clients;

Job Requirements:
- Certified graduate from renowned universities in finance/accounting/law;
- MUST HAVE PROFESSIONAL QUALIFICATIONS:
o Accounting Practitioner Certificate (APC),
o Certified Public Accountant (CPA) and/or Certificate for Practicing Services on Tax Procedures (Tax Agent)
o Adequate number of updating hours (minimum 24 hours per year) as required to be fully licensed.
- Membership in an international accounting body such as ACCA, CPA (Australia), or ICAEW is an advantage;
- Minimum 3+ years of work experience in tax advisory practices for international auditing, consulting or law firms;
- Proven experience as team or project manager in consulting firms with international clients is a big plus as we are also looking for competent team leaders;
- Solid understanding of Vietnamese tax regulations, OECD Transfer Pricing Guidelines, Base Erosion and Profit Shifting (BEPS) Actions as well as international tax practices;
- Proven ability to apply these frameworks to cross-border transactions, assessments of permanent establishment, and group tax planning;
- Exceptional oral and written skills both, in English and Vietnamese;
- Professionalism, dedication, integrity and trustworthiness;
- Ability to multi-task under high pressure, and to complete assignments within time constraints and deadlines;
- Long term commitment in a fast-paced, rapidly growing and international/multicultural work environment.

*Your Benefits
As a team member of our team, you will be entitled to the following benefits:
- Competitive salary (based on relevant work experience and professional qualifications);
- Comprehensive private health insurance;
- 13th monthly salary and annual performance-based bonuses;
- Annual salary reviews/raises based on professional performance and individual success;
- Fast professional development and career progression/promotion;
- Prime office location in the heart of Ho Chi Minh City;
- Above-average annual leave allowance;
- Opportunity to work in an international law firm with well-known and prestigious international clients;
- Gain experience across various legal practice areas under supervision of international legal experts;
- High level of responsibility and independence in handling client matters.

Job Description:
